reviews.review_text:
Recording Stats for 9.16.91 Mastered live FOB DFC from:
Set One:    Section 2   Row U   Seat 1 & 2
Set Two:    Section 3   Row T   Seat 13 & 14
by Clay C. Brennecke and James Young using: 
B&K 4011 cardioids at 110 degrees handheld both Sets > Neumann BS 48i-2 Phantom Power Supply > Modified Sony TCD D-10 Professional DAT machine

zip file corrupt downloading the individual shn files worked, but the zip file of the entire show did not.

BTW, the recording and show are both quite awesome!  unusual set list and spirited playing.  these guys nailed the recording as well.

Glad it's back! I started to download the SBD, went away for Thanksgiving, and poof, everything was gone.  I am ecstatic that the powers that be put the audience recordings back! This was my only "Comes a Time" and ever since this MSG run I have searched for this show.  IMO the Dead have the right to control their soundboards, but let the audience tapes run free, please, because I'll never feel the way I felt at this show again.  However, owning this is the next best thing.
Great show! Good sound and excellent set from the Dead. Thanks for adding it to the Archive.

Clarity, balance, fine show ...and a little rough playing at times but a great recording to catch it all.  Audience singalongs come through like a beautiful backing vocal.  Nice spirited defense of the mics recorded live -- Thank you Brennecke and Young for the work that goes into the recording and transfer of the fine material we have here.  
     One year post-Brent and the show lacks the verve Brent was bringing so I wasn't appreciating this phase of the Dead as much as I do now.  This is a good show.  I wish I could remember why I found it.
whoa if you listen closely during It Must Have Been the Roses i think someone near the taper is having a baby.  awesome

s1 vg, s2 ok s1 is very good, exciting. S2 is a bit more of a mess with aggressive Hornsby keyboards overrunning tunes he doesn't fully know (Saint & Comes a Time especially), and Garcia sort of defers to him unfortunately.
ya i heard a drum too :) i never heard anything like i heard in this run and i fetched Uncle Miltie a sandwich once.  :)
